tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The results show severe arterial acidemia (arterial pH 7.0, low O₂ saturation), with normal pCO₂ and bicarbonate, suggesting a primary metabolic acidosis. Oxygenation is slightly reduced. Venous blood gases and electrolytes are within normal limits. Immediate clinical evaluation is recommended due to the life-threatening low arterial pH.
